2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The proposed scheme involves quantization and multicast of overheard interferences, which are key techniques used in network communication. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with a multiple-input single-output broadcast channel, which is a common model in social and information networks. 
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The optimization of degrees of freedom in a MISO broadcast channel involves mathematical modeling and analysis, which are common in computational engineering and science. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The proposed scheme involves broadcasting new private messages, which is a common application in multimedia communication.
